<a href="AmPol_Syllabus_Sum14.pdf">Syllabus</a>
<br>
<!-- Course Description
&nbsp &nbsp <a onclick ="javascript:ShowHide('Course3')" href="javascript:;" >Course Description</a>, <a href="CongPol_SyllabusF13_20131103.doc"> Syllabus </a>
<span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Helvetica;">
<div class="mid" id="Course3" style="DISPLAY: none" >
This course introduces students to the US Congress with a focus on thinking analytically about the determinants of Congressional behavior. Among the factors examined will be the characteristics and incentives of legislators, rules governing the legislative process and internal organization, separation of powers, political parties, Congressional elections, and interest group influence. A background in analytical methods will be helpful but is not required.</div>
